Sentiment-Analysis-on-Twitter-US-2020-Elections

This is a sentiment analysis on the Twitter US 2020 election environment using Python. 
It takes tweets as inputs and evaluates who the tweet relates to and whether the sentiment is positive or negative. 
The files corpus.txt, stop_words.txt, and us_election_tweets were provided by the University of Toronto Faculty of Information from the INF1340H course. 
		
This project focuses on the following:
	- Clean and parse the tweets
	- Determin the candidate relation
	- Determine the sentiment score from 0 to 1
	- Predict the number of supporters for each candidate
	- Analyze the popularity of each candidate throughout the months
	- Visualize the most commonly used words for each candidate
